body:
### What Is SoccerAgent?
SoccerAgent is an agent that can be used to play football in robocup soccer simulations. It is based off the standard AgentBase in the TinMan framework but has a number of improvements aimed at making it easier to get started playing soccer!

### Installation - Windows Only
Install [Visual Studio 2012](http://www.microsoft.com/visualstudio/eng/downloads)

Install the [Visual Studio C++ 2008 Redistributable Package (x86)](http://www.microsoft.com/en-us/download/details.aspx?id=29)

Install [simspark](http://sourceforge.net/projects/simspark/files/simspark/0.2.2/simspark-0.2.2-win32.exe/download)

Install [rcssserver3d](http://sourceforge.net/projects/simspark/files/rcssserver3d/0.6.5/rcssserver3d-0.6.5-win32.exe/download)

Modify setSenseMyPos in C:\Program Files (x86)\rcssserver3d 0.6.5\share\rcssserver3d\rsg\agent\nao from false to true.

Install [Ruby](http://rubyforge.org/frs/download.php/76798/rubyinstaller-1.9.3-p392.exe) (Check the option to add Ruby to PATH).

Restart your machine

Download and open the [SoccerAgent Solution](https://github.com/TVOHM/Robocup/zipball/master)

### Getting Started
To start programming your agent, you need to modify MySoccerAgent.cs

```
    class MySoccerAgent : SoccerAgentBase
    {
        public override void SoccerAgentThink(PerceptorState perceptorState, AgentState agentState)
        {
            switch (agentState)
            {
                case AgentState.IDLE:
                    // The agent is doing nothing.
                    // Start a keyframe action - SetKeyFrame("kick");
                    // Or tell the agent to walk - MoveTo(Landmark.FlagRightTop);
                    break;
                case AgentState.WALKING:
                    // The agent is walking
                    // You may update the walking target / behaviour MoveTo(perceptorState.BallPosition);
                    // Stop the walk - MoveStop();
                    // Or interrupt the walk by starting a keyframe action - SetKeyFrame("kick");
                    break;
                case AgentState.KEYFRAME:
                    // The agent is performing a keyframe animation that was started by SetKeyFrame
                    // You may not take any actions
                    break;
                case AgentState.AUTORIGHTING:
                    // The agent has fallen over and is in the process of getting up
                    // You may not take any actions
                    break;
            }
        }
    }
```
